  "conclusion": "Chosen mechanism: the (type, semanticMeaning?) split. Writ links carry a human-readable `type` field (the label, kept as-is from today's schema) and an optional `semanticMeaning` field that references a plugin-owned registered meaning. See child click conclusions for parameter decisions:\n\n- c-mo2db4n7 — split design (label + optional contract reference)\n- c-mo2dbdnw — meaning assignment is EXPLICIT (author declares, never inferred)\n- c-mo2dbd3d — pairing policy is OPEN (no name-meaning validation)\n- c-mo2dbea3 — normalization: lowercase space-delimited canonical form\n- c-mo2dbey3 — polarity lives in the meaning schema; names carry no direction metadata\n\nImplementation direction established in session:\n- Keep existing `WritLinkDoc.type` field (no rename) — its role shifts from \"structural type\" to \"human-readable label\"; normalization applied in place\n- Add optional `semanticMeaning?: string` field (id reference) to WritLinkDoc\n- Clerk owns the meaning registry; meanings are declared as plugin-manifest kit contributions\n- Meaning id format: plugin-qualified with `.` separator (e.g. `spider.precedence-gate`), matching the existing role id convention\n- Meaning registry schema is minimal: `{id, ownerPlugin, description}` — direction/cardinality/hooks deferred until a second consumer or cross-plugin coordination creates actual demand\n\nBrief forthcoming for the substrate work (schema change + normalization + registry primitive + migration). Declaring specific meanings (e.g. `spider.precedence-gate`) and wiring Spider to consume them are separate briefs.",
